# ⚙️ ToolHub

> **AI Tool Registry — Secure, Semantic, Self-healing**
> Zero config → working agent with 2 tools in 7 lines of code.

ToolHub fixes the three gaps in today's MCP ecosystem:

| Gap | ToolHub solution |
|-----|-----------------|
| 41% of tools have no auth | Security scoring — tools below 40/100 are **rejected at registration** |
| Zero observability | Every call logged — latency, errors, agent ID, 30-day trends |
| No semantic discovery | Plain-English search via cosine similarity + composite ranking |

---

## Project structure

```
toolhub/
├── server/                         Node.js / Express backend
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── db/
│   │   │   ├── schema.sql          ← single canonical schema (7 tables)
│   │   │   ├── index.js            pg pool
│   │   │   ├── migrate.js          npm run migrate
│   │   │   └── seed.js             npm run seed  (10 tools)
│   │   ├── routes/
│   │   │   ├── tools.js            CRUD + /search + /health + /invoke-config
│   │   │   ├── credentials.js      AES-256-GCM vault
│   │   │   ├── analytics.js        observability queries
│   │   │   └── webhooks.js         change notifications
│   │   ├── services/
│   │   │   ├── security.js         encrypt/decrypt, score, schema diff, HMAC
│   │   │   ├── tokens.js           15-min JWT invoke tokens
│   │   │   ├── embeddings.js       TF-IDF semantic search + in-memory cache
│   │   │   └── webhooks.js         outbound webhook firing
│   │   ├── middleware/
│   │   │   └── analytics.js        auto-log every tool call
│   │   ├── jobs/
│   │   │   └── healthMonitor.js    cron every 6h, degradation + restore
│   │   └── index.js                Express entry point
│   ├── .env.example
│   └── package.json
│
├── sdk/                            pip install toolhub-sdk
│   ├── toolhub_sdk/
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │   ├── models.py               Tool, InvokeResult
│   │   └── client.py               ToolHub — search, get, list, invoke,
│   │                               register_credential, as_langchain_tool,
